# Knock

knock is a simple tool to add an alert to run at specific time. It is useful to remind you to do something at specific time.

## Installation

- Clone the repository
- Depending on your system, you can run the following command to install the package

```bash
# For Linux-x64
make install/linux-x64
# For Linux-x86
make install/linux-x86
# For Windows-x64
make install/windows-x64
# For Windows-x86
make install/windows-x86
```

## Usage

- To add a new alert, run the following command

```bash
# knock -d <duration> -m <message>
knock -d "15s" -m "Hello World" # This will add an alert to run after 15 seconds
knock -d "1h" -m "Hello World" # This will add an alert to run after 1 hour
knock -d "1m" -m "Hello World" # This will add an alert to run after 1 minute
```
